 Kcmgrub2 - a control module to configure the GRUB2 bootloader
===============================================================

 DEPENDENCIES
==============

Required:
 * KDE-Libs 4.4 + KDE-Base-runtime 4.4 (or newer)
   http://www.kde.org

 * Qt 4.6 (or newer)
   http://qt.nokia.com/

 * Python 2.6 - 2.7
   http://www.python.org

 * PyQt
   http://www.riverbankcomputing.co.uk/software/pyqt/

 * PyKDE
   http://techbase.kde.org/Development/Languages/Python

Optional:
 * Python-xlib
   http://python-xlib.sourceforge.net/

Please note that if compiling from source you also need to install -dev/-devel
versions of KDE-Libs, KDE-Base-Runtime and Qt, depending on your distribution.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

 COMPILATION AND INSTALLATION
==============================

Open a terminal in the kcmgrub2 directory and type:

mkdir build
cd build
cmake .. -DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=`kde4-config --prefix`
make
make install (as root)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
